---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Support — Runlab" description="Get help with Runlab. Contact support, learn how to delete your account, and find answers to common questions.">
  <div class="support-page">
    <div class="support-content">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="support-header">
        <h1>Support</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Need help? We're here for you.</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For questions, feedback, or support requests, reach us at:</p>
        <a href="mailto:support@runlab.fit" class="contact-email">support@runlab.fit</a>
      </section>

      <!-- Account Deletion -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li>Open the Runlab app on your iPhone</li>
          <li>Navigate to your Profile tab</li>
          <li>Scroll down and tap "Delete Account"</li>
          <li>Type "delete my account" exactly as shown to confirm</li>
          <li>Tap the "Delete Account" button to confirm</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="warning-callout">
          <p>&#9888; Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone. All your data will be removed, including activities, health snapshots, AI coaching history, training plans, and your athlete profile.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I connect my Strava account?</summary>
          <p>Open Runlab, go to Profile, and tap 'Connect Strava.' You'll be redirected to Strava to authorize read-only access to your running activities. Runlab syncs your runs automatically after connection.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What Apple Health data does Runlab access?</summary>
          <p>Runlab reads the following data from Apple Health (read-only, never writes back): Heart Rate Variability (HRV), Resting Heart Rate, Sleep Analysis, VO2 Max, Body Mass, and Active Energy Burned. This data helps the AI Coach provide personalized recovery and training recommendations. You can revoke access anytime in iOS Settings > Privacy > Health.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I manage my subscription?</summary>
          <p>Runlab subscriptions are managed through the Apple App Store. To change or cancel your plan, go to iPhone Settings > Apple ID > Subscriptions > Runlab. Free tier users can upgrade to Runlab Elite ($4.99/month or $44.99/year) from within the app.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How is my data protected?</summary>
          <p>Your data is encrypted in transit (HTTPS/TLS) and stored securely on Supabase with row-level security, meaning only you can access your data. Health data is never stored in iCloud. When the AI Coach processes your data, it's sent securely to the Anthropic Claude API — it's not used for model training and not stored beyond your request. We never sell your data. See our Privacy Policy for full details.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I delete my account?</summary>
          <p>Go to Profile in the Runlab app, tap 'Delete Account,' and type 'delete my account' to confirm. This permanently removes all your data including activities, health snapshots, coaching history, and training plans. This action cannot be undone.</p>
        </details>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .support-page {
    padding: 80px 24px;
  }

  .support-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .support-header {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .support-header h1 {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .support-header .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
  }

  .section p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
  }

  .contact-email {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-brand-blue);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 4px;
    transition: text-decoration 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-email:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .steps {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 24px 0;
  }

  .steps li {
    padding: 4px 0;
  }

  .warning-callout {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-alert-red);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .warning-callout p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(51, 97, 193, 0.15);
    padding: 16px 0;
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    content: '-';
  }

  .faq-item p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    padding-top: 12px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
